OL,3,CHetty Pit: #300,000 project to restore
OL,4,Chistoric colliery site
OL,6,FWhile coal raising ceased in the
OL,7,F1920s, the shaft was retained for
OL,8,Fventilation and a second means of
OL,9,Fentry for the nearby Tymawr Colliery.
OL,11,FLater merged with Lewis Merthyr
OL,12,FColliery (now the Rhondda Heritage
OL,13,FPark), the Hetty buildings were
OL,14,Ffinally decommissioned upon the
OL,15,Fcomplex's closure in 1983.
OL,17,FAlthough a preservation order was
OL,18,Fapplied soon after closure, the Hetty
OL,19,Fsite was effectively abandoned and
OL,20,Ffell victim to vandalism in the years
OL,21,Fthat followed.
