OL,3,CHetty Pit: #300,000 project to restore
OL,4,Chistoric colliery site
OL,6,F"I'm glad to say that there are a lot
OL,7,Fof people visiting now from all over
OL,8,Fthe country and from Europe because of
OL,9,Fthe history behind the the engine and
OL,10,Fwhat remains here".
OL,12,FWork has already been carried out by
OL,13,Fcontractors to replace deteriorated
OL,14,Fsections on the lower levels of the
OL,15,Fheadframe, while the new air
OL,16,Fcompressor has arrived on site ready
OL,17,Fto power the engine.
OL,19,FUntil now, the Trust has had to hire a
OL,20,Fcompressor to run the engine on an
OL,21,Foccasional basis.
