OL,3,CHetty Pit: #300,000 project to restore
OL,4,Chistoric colliery site
OL,6,F"He loved things like this. He was
OL,7,Fdedicated to history. He would do
OL,8,Fanything to tell the story of this
OL,9,Fplace - he was a master of it."
OL,11,F"I think he would be very pleased and
OL,12,Famazed at the progress we've made."
OL,14,FWhile there is still considerable work
OL,15,Fto be done, the Trust hope to
OL,16,Fofficially open the new compressor in
OL,17,Fearly 2025.
